#5. Application Specifications
a. Architecture
The system follows a three-tier architecture:
Frontend (User Interface): Handles user interaction and displays the map and parking data
Backend (Server): Processes requests, handles business logic, and communicates with the database
Database: Stores parking data and user-related information
The frontend sends requests to the backend, which processes the data and retrieves relevant information from the database before returning results to the user.

b. Database Model
The database includes the following main tables:
Users (user_id, email, password)
ParkingSpaces (parking_id, location, availability_status)
Locations (location_id, name, coordinates)
Relationships:
Each parking space is linked to a location
Each user can perform multiple searches
Constraints:
User email must be unique
Parking spaces must have valid location references

c. Technologies Used
Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
Chosen for creating a responsive and interactive interface
Backend: Python 
Chosen for handling logic and scalability
Database: MySQL
Efficient for structured data storage
Map Integration: Google Maps API (or similar)
Used to display parking locations visually

d. User Interface Design
The application includes:
A home/search page where users enter a location
A map interface displaying nearby parking spaces
Clear markers showing available parking spots
The design is simple, clean, and user-friendly, with easy navigation and minimal steps required to perform a search.

e. Security Measures
User authentication for secure access 
Passwords are encrypted before storage
Input validation to prevent invalid or harmful data
Secure communication between frontend and backend

